<p><b>Adangme</b> (also called <b>Dangme</b>), is a <a href="/wiki/Kwa_languages" title="Kwa languages">Kwa language</a> spoken in south-eastern <a href="/wiki/Ghana" title="Ghana">Ghana</a> by 800,000 people.</p>
<p>Some sources list <b>Adangbe</b> as another name for the same language whereas <a href="http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=adq" class="external text" rel="nofollow">Ethnologue</a> lists it as a different language in the Left bank branch of the Kwa family, and it has a separate <a href="/wiki/ISO_639-3" title="ISO 639-3">ISO 639-3</a> code of 'adq'.</p>
