<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Classification">Classification</span></h2>
<p>Adangme is a <a href="/wiki/Kwa_languages" title="Kwa languages">Kwa language</a>, part of the <a href="/wiki/Niger-Congo_languages" title="Niger-Congo languages">Niger-Congo family</a>. It is very closely related to <a href="/wiki/Ga_language" title="Ga language">Ga</a>, and together they form the <a href="/wiki/Ga-Dangme_languages" title="Ga-Dangme languages" class="mw-redirect">Ga-Dangme</a> branch within Kwa.</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Geographic_distribution">Geographic distribution</span></h2>
<p>Adangme is spoken in <a href="/wiki/Ghana" title="Ghana">Ghana</a> by 800,000 people.</p>
<p>There are six main dialects which coincide with political divisions. The coastal dialects are Ada, Ningo and Prampram (Gbugbla). The inland dialects are Shai (<span class="Unicode">Sɛ</span>), Krobo (Klo) and Osudoku.</p>
